SpringBoot : = It is a java framework which is used to build backend application easily and quickly.

Spring Boot is a framework that simplifies the development of Java applications by providing auto-configuration and embedded servers.

Spring Boot helps you:
   Create REST APIs
   Connect to databases
   Handle authentication
   Build microservices
   With very little configuration.

   Before vs After Spring Boot
    Without Spring Boot (old Spring)
       Lots of XML
       Manual server setup
       Too much configuration

    With Spring Boot
       No XML
       No server install
       Just write code and run



   What happens when Spring Boot application starts ?
    => When spring boot application starts :-
      1. Main method gets execute .
      2. Spring creates @ApplicationContext (IoC container)
              It is responsible for managing beans , handling DI and managinglifecycle.
      3. Component scanning happens .
          Finds classes with @RestController , @Service , @Repository etc.
      4. Beans are created 
          Objects are created and stored in container .
      5. Dependencies are injected.
          Controller -> Service -> Repository
      6. Embedded server (Tomcat) starts
          Application is ready to handle requests.

    When Spring Boot starts, it creates the IoC container, scans components, creates and injects beans, applies auto-configuration, starts the embedded server, and becomes ready to handle requests.
